race.description: Ladbrokes Future Stars Series Heat 4 Maiden Plate
race.comment: BLANKFIELD (1) has placed in all three runs to date and looks well placed to break through. He's been in the market his past couple and was beaten under a length last start at Pakenham in an encouraging effort. This doesn't look like it'll take much more winning. ROUGH ENUFF (7) is the clear danger. His debut at Pakenham was very good over 1200m when finding the line strongly, and 1400m here should suit ideally. He draws much better this time around and could sit closer. PAFITIS (6) resumed with a solid run here in a distant third. He took on some handy races as a 2yo and could be a quick improver. NOSTRO ROCCIA (5) wasn't beaten far fresh at Terang and should be fitter getting every chance up top from the inside gate. FASTOBID (3) can run well on debut.
